HEADWORD: Wareless
<hw>Ware"less</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Ware</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>Unwary; incautious; unheeding; careless;
unaware.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And <qex>wareless</qex> of the evil⟦br⟧
That by themselves unto themselves is wrought.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Warely</ent>⟦br⟧
